      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the goblin tangents; my brain just defaults to the chaotic energy of the craft! The pattern on the circle moves by rotating through perfect fifths, or in reverse, perfect fourths. If you start at C, moving up a fifth takes you to G, and from G, another fifth takes you to D. The circle simply dictates which scale degrees naturally relate to another; every key is connected to another key by these fundamental intervals, like the relationship between the main hobbit settlement and the nearest, slightly less tidy mushroom hut. This smooth rotational pattern explains why certain chords sound comfortable next to each other.",
